# Autobot project structure

Autobot is a **single deployable app** (the `autobot/` package) that runs on one ARM Linux box, plus a
one-time credential tool. There is no separate Pi "bridge" / PC "brain" anymore — but keep the internal
layer boundaries. **Never blur them.**

```
autobot/                 # the one app (python -m autobot)
  __main__.py            #   entrypoint
  config.py              #   all config + UI-settable state (NO secrets); robot_link = native|mock
  credentials.py         #   the ONLY loader of robot secrets; masked, never sent to UI/provider
  robot/                 #   the ONLY code that touches the robot
    link.py              #     RobotLink contract + make_link() factory
    native_link.py       #     NativeRobotLink: native TUTK bridge + ffmpeg/mediamtx + deadman (owns secrets)
    mock_link.py         #     MockRobotLink: fake robot for hardware-free dev
    frames.py            #     MAVLink builders + PARAM_TOGGLES + EYE_ANIMATIONS (protocol source of truth)
    video.py             #     mediamtx config + ffmpeg helpers + WHEP/HLS upstreams + stream auth
    mqtt.py              #     optional Home Assistant entities (native only)
    native/              #     ebo_bridge.c (native TUTK), mediamtx.template.yml, build_bridge.sh, probe_eyes.py
  brain/                 #   the AI agent loop + safety floor (calls the robot only via a RobotLink)
    agent.py             #     event-driven perceive->think->act->observe; reflex+cortex (hybrid); scheduler
    perception.py        #     snapshot + telemetry (+ VSLAM pose) -> Observation
    safety.py            #     clamps, rate limit, deadman, autonomy + talk gating
    curiosity.py         #     scene novelty + action repetition + visited-cell coverage -> anti-repeat nudge
    memory.py            #     persistent memory: facts + daily log + sightings (atomic, rotation, embed recall)
    embeddings.py        #     optional local embedding backend for semantic recall (AUTOBOT_EMBED_MODEL)
    tasks.py             #     persistent scheduled tasks/reminders + scheduling math (TaskStore)
    slam.py              #     lightweight monocular visual odometry (pose + keyframes; advisory)
    vlm_client.py        #     client for the VLM "eyes" service (hybrid perception) -> scripts/vlm_service.py
    identity.py          #     owner authority / pairing / approval flow (enforced with safety)
    tts.py               #     text-to-speech -> G.711 (for talkback)
    providers/           #     OpenAI-compatible LLM client(s)
    skills/              #     capabilities as Skills + the SkillRegistry (the action contract)
      core.py            #       body controls (drive/stop/say/eyes/toggles/dock/...)
      memory_skill.py    #       remember/recall/forget
      home_assistant.py  #       control HA devices (list/get_state/on-off/any service; optional: HASS_*)
      recognition.py     #       face recog (insightface|face_recognition) + sightings + greet-by-name
      voice.py           #       mic STT -> 'heard' speech (optional: faster-whisper)
      places.py          #       named places + go_to_place (clamped steps) + topological graph
      patrol.py          #       smart patrol mode; tasks_skill.py: schedule reminders/routines
      mcp_skill.py       #       expose external MCP server tools to the cortex (AUTOBOT_MCP_SERVERS)
  web/                   #   the web layer
    server.py            #     FastAPI: REST + WebSocket + video proxy, serves the UI; owns LINK + brain
    static/fallback.html
webui/                   # React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind. Thin client, same-origin.
collector/               # One-time credential capture (being reworked for mDNS). Writes top-level .env + vendor/.
  apk_patch/ pc_frida/ hooks/ bionic/ receiver.py
deploy/pi-gen/           # Turnkey RPi 4 appliance image: pi-gen config + stage-autobot + build-wsl.sh
vendor/                  # GITIGNORED: TUTK .so, bionic runtime, ioctl9930.bin (you provide)
Dockerfile, docker-compose.yml, run.sh, requirements.txt, .env.example
docs/                    # ARCHITECTURE, BRIDGE_PROTOCOL, AI_BRAIN, SAFETY, COLLECTOR, SETUP, PROVENANCE
.cursor/rules/           # these rules
```

## Where to add things

- **New robot capability**: add the frame/IOCTL in `autobot/robot/frames.py` (+ `native/ebo_bridge.c` if it
  needs a new control kind), handle it in `NativeRobotLink._do_action` (and `MockRobotLink`), document in
  `docs/BRIDGE_PROTOCOL.md`, THEN add an AI tool in `autobot/brain/tools.py`, THEN a UI control. Never touch
  the robot from anywhere but `autobot/robot/`.
- **New AI capability**: add/extend a `Skill` in `autobot/brain/skills/` (register in
  `build_default_skills()`), set each tool's authority, keep heavy deps optional + graceful.
- **New AI loop behavior**: edit `autobot/brain/agent.py` + the system prompt.
- **New telemetry field**: `RobotLink.telemetry()` (both impls) -> `Observation` in `perception.py` -> UI.
- **New config knob**: `autobot/config.py` (env + UI override) -> surface in the UI config panel.

## Data flow (one direction of truth)

robot ⇄ ebo_bridge.c ⇄ NativeRobotLink ⇄ (RobotLink) ⇄ agent.py / web server (WS) ⇄ webui.
The AI provider is called only from `brain/providers/` via `agent.py`. Secrets load only in
`credentials.py` and are consumed only by `NativeRobotLink`.
